insert into cfg_5_2.requestdata (id, title, "Request_ID", "Status", "Project_Description", "CFG_Member?", "Requester_First_Name", "Requester_Last_Name", "447911925", "1339104825", "Assigned_First_Name", "Assigned_Last_Name", "Requester_Email", "Request_Date", "Institution", "Shipping_Address", "CFG_Core", "Amount_Requested", "-643239159", "2039874986", "-1235327866", "GBP_being_Addressed", "5943919") values (6, E'cfg_rRequest_3068', E'cfg_rRequest_3068', E'Approved', E'The purpose of this request is to analyze monoclonal antibodies that have been shown to clearly bind alpha-1-3 linear and branched glycans.', E'Yes subgroups :To Be Assigned', E'John', E'Kearney', E'John', E'Kearney', E'John', E'Kearney', E'jfk@uab.edu', E'05/23/2014', E'University of Alabama at Birmingham', E'410 Shelby Building University of Alabama at Birmingham Birmingham, Al 35294 2059346557', E'H', E'', E'My lab has accumulated a large number of purified monoclonal antibodies mostly of IgM,IgG3 and IgA isotypes to a variety of carbohydrates expressed on capsules or cell walls of S. pneumonia, Groups A and B streptococci, Enterobacter, B subtilis. We know the fine specificities of some of these include alpha 1-3 glucans, GlcNAc containing polysaccharides, sialylated oligosaccharides. We have found recently that a lot of these of these bind Aspergillus fumigatus and as well as protecting against infections induced by the organisms used to raise these Mabs they can protect against A. fumigatus induced airway disease in mouse models for which we are funded by NIAID grant R01 AI14782-34 (3/1/011-2/28/16), and another one to study infant antibody response to bacterial polysaccharides, 1R01AI100005-01(3/1/12 – 2/28/17). I would like to test these Mabs on glycan arrays to determine their reactivity to a wider array of glycans which would give us valuable information to help study their role in interacting with other organisms (including self glycoprotein antigens). In this request we wish to ascertain the fine specificity of a series of monoclonal antibodies which have nominal reactivity with alpha1-3 glucose containing polysaccharides. They are highly purified from serum free hybridoma supernatant by monoclonal anti-mouse IgM or IgA and protein G -Sepharose columns. Since this panel contains multiple isotypes it would be best to use a secondary anti-Mouse Ig antibody that reacts with all mouse Ig isotypes.', E'Y', E'David Smith', E'Data on five monoclonal antibodies I am wish to submit that have been shown to clearly bind alpha-1-3 linear and branched glycans by nigerotriose inhibitable ELISA assays. Mab: A16 (IgM, lambda) Derivation: BALB/J mice immunized with alpha1-3 dextran Source: Hybridoma grown in serum free Gibco HB medium Purification: Affinity chromatography from monoclonal anti-Mouse IgM Sepharose, eluted at acid pH Biological Activity: Binds to Enterobacter cloacae and A. fumigatus brightly by flow cytometry. Nominal specificity: alpha 1-3 glucans Preparation: Purified IgM Mab: 1-21 (IgM, lambda) Derivation: BALB/J mice immunized with bacterial derived &#945;1-3 glucan Source: Hybridoma grown in serum free Gibco HB medium Purification: Affinity chromatography from monoclonal anti-Mouse IgM Sepharose, eluted at acid pH Biological Activity: Binds Enterobacter cloacae and A. fumigatus brightly by flow cytometry Nominal specificity: &#945;1-3 glucan-containing molecules Preparation: Purified IgM Mab: 8-21 (IgG2b, lambda) Derivation: BALB/J mice immunized with bacterial derived &#945;1-3 glucan Source: Hybridoma grown in serum free Gibco HB medium Purification: Affinity chromatography Protein G column - Sepharose, eluted at acid pH Biological Activity: Binds A. fumigatus Nominal specificity: &#945;1-3 glucan-containing molecules Preparation: Purified IgG2b Mab: J558 (IgA, lambda) Derivation: BALB/J mice plasmacytoma with specificity to &#945;1-3 glucan Source: Plasmacytoma grown in serum free Gibco HB medium Purification: Affinity chromatography anti-Mouse IgA-sepharose column - Sepharose, eluted at acid pH Biological Activity: Binds A. fumigatus, bacteria Nominal specificity: &#945;1-3 glucan-containing molecules Preparation: Purified IgA Mab: S1ae7 (IgM, kappa) Derivation: BALB/J mice hybridoma with specificity to Group B (1a) streptococci Source: Hybridoma grown in serum free Gibco HB medium Purification: Affinity chromatography anti-Mouse IgM-sepharose column - Sepharose, eluted at acid pH Biological Activity: Binds A. fumigatus, bacteria Nominal specificity: oligosaccharide Preparation: Purified IgM', E'* 1. Define the specificity and affinity for carbohydrate ligands');
